<action name=SNTP(8)>SNTP(8)</action>                                                   <action name=SNTP(8)>SNTP(8)</action>

NAME
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            sntp - simple network time protocol client

SYNOPSIS
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            ip/sntp \[ -di \] \[ server \]

DESCRIPTION
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            Sntp is a simple client for the Simple Network Time Protocol
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            (RFC1361). It requests the time from the SNTP service on
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            server (default: udp!$ntp!ntp), and if it receives a
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            plausible reply, sets the local time accordingly, in both
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            <action name=rtc(3)>rtc(3)</action> and /dev/time. The -d option prints debugging text,
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            including the time received\; the -i option stops sntp from
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            actually updating the local time.

FILES
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            #r/rtc
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            /dev/time

SOURCE
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            /appl/cmd/ip/sntp.b

SEE ALSO
<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>            <action name=date(1)>date(1)</action>, <action name=cons(3)>cons(3)</action>

<style color=#00ffffff size=1>.</style>                                Inferno Manual
